cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimizing WLANs and improving network performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper uses control theory to develop adaptive algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses adapting contention parameters to network conditions. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on security concerns related to WLANs. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possibility as the paper evaluates the performance of the adaptive algorithms compared to standard configurations.
